From Richard Krehbiel Subject Re IDE vs SCSI In article GRUBB writes Richard Krehbiel writes Stuff about the connection between IDE and IDA deleated clock bit width If IDE speed come from IDA WHERE does the s sighted for IDE come from Well some quick math on my part shows that an bus bits wide performing a transfer every two clock cycles will provide bytes Someone said that it really takes clock cycles to perform a transfer so that reduces the transfer rate to s which is the commonly used figure for ISA bus However I believe a two clock transfer is possible wait states Richard Krehbiel OS will do for me until AmigaDOS for the comes